args: Please note that this story contains spoilers\nfor the Accursed Archives event.

After Lathna unexpectedly runs away, Curran
and Heinwald set off after her and arrive in a
place called Teinsom, which is also known as
the Immortal Village. But as they enter, a pack
of scary locals surrounds them.
From what do you flee?\nWe are not your enemy.\nYou are not our sacrifice.

We are fragments. We two are one,
with wings and sight shared betwixt.
Slumbering corpses of trance within
a single cradle.

If the posted sign is plucked,
obfuscous becomes the path.
Accept the name prescribed you.
Accept the name of...
N Y A R L A T H O T E P
Heinwald! Heeeeinwald! I've got a case\nthat you're gonna want to see, pronto!
Well this is sudden. I trust I can expect\na sufficiently interesting case if you have\ncome requesting my aid.
The one from the Case of the Accursed\nArchives? Fascinating. Was she stolen\naway in the night or somesuch?
Witnesses say she left of her own accord.
Why do you waste my time with this\nfeckless drivel, Curran? I have no interest\nin seeking out sad runaway girls.

＂We are Chaos. We are the silver key that
swings wide the gate. We are the crimson
carpet of purity and befoulment stretched
out upon the place of His advent.＂
Evidently, that's what Lathna said just\nbefore she made like a bee and buzzed off.
Doesn't that particular brand of nonsense\nremind you of a certain someone?
Indeed it does. Perhaps your meager mind\nhas brought me an interesting case after\nall, Curran. Well done.
Er, thanks, I guess? So, what does this\nmean? I thought Lathna was just a regular\ngirl from a regular village.
Ah, but remember that in our previous\ncase, the dragon Nyarlathotep took pains\nto assume her appearance.

If we suppose that was no mere
coincidence... Or if we go a step further
and assume they were resonating with
one another for some reason...
Chaos... The key... The Ancient One...\nHa! How intriguing this all is!
Er, perhaps you could hold off on the\ndetours into your weirdo world until\nAFTER we're done with the sleuthing?

Oh, please, Curran. If this case were
one that could be solved here on the
spot, you wouldn't have come to me
in the first place, now would you?
Heh. I suppose you got me there.\nShould we get to searching, then?
＂Get to searching＂ implies you have\nno idea where the girl might be.\nIs this, in fact, the case?
No, I have a pretty good idea\nwhere she's gone.
Then there is no need for me to\nspecifically go, is there?
Look. I asked for you help because I know\nyou like tough cases, and this is definitely\none of those.
Lathna was headed to a village\ncalled Teinsom, which is also known as...
Curran? When are we going to arrive in\nthis Teinsom village of yours?

Shouldn't be too long now! ...Er, but
seeing as how it's not on any known
map, that estimate might be a touch
optimistic on my part.
What manner of place IS this village,\nanyway? It certainly has a rather\noutrageous appellation.
According to rumor, anyone who visits\nthe village can gain eternal life.

Ah, I see. That's not the most unusual tale
I've ever heard sprung from a secluded
region—yet one I would take with the
entire salt shaker and not just a grain.
Fifty years ago, an old man from a fishing\nvillage near Saint Lotier supposedly set\noff on a journey to Teinsom.
When he left, he was more than eighty.\nBut when he returned recently, he looked\nlike a man of significantly younger years.
Very well, I will bite. What happened\nto this supposedly 130-year-old man?
He disappeared suddenly into the night—\nand his family along with him.

The next morning, some neighboring
villagers found the bodies of the family.
They appeared to have been mauled
by some kind of giant beast.
However, the body of the old man was\nnever found—not the old version,\nnor the youthful.

I hear some villagers had reported seeing
a colossal monster earlier that evening.
Everyone assumed they were just seeing
things, but in the morning...
I see. And now you have decided to\ndrag ME to this questionable village.
Because I knew you'd be thrilled! I mean,\ncome on—this place is right up your\nspooky weirdo alley.
Oh, I won't deny a healthy interest—\nI merely wish the village had been\nlocated a bit closer to home.
I can't believe that you fast-talked me,\nof all people, into coming to such a\nremote and desolate place.
If you walked as fast as you griped,\nwe'd already be there by now.
A true statement, but alas, a dull one.\nWait, does that mean the truth is dull?\nGood heavens!
Zip it and walk, pal, unless you wanna\nbe hoofing it for the next yea... Huh?
There's someone on the ground there.
It's Lathna! What is she doing collapsed\nall the way out here?!
She's burning up with fever. We need\nto get here somewhere safe, now!
Then it seems this village of yours\nis our only workable option.
Right. Time to get busy, feet!
So this is Teinsom, mmm? It all seems\nrather unassuming at first blink.
We'll worry about the village later.\nFirst, let's find an inn or something\nwhere Lathna can rest.
...And right on time, a villager approaches!\nYou there! Hello! We need help!
Be gone... Be gone... Be gone...
What the heck is going on here?!
